{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.4",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 4",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 4 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:1",
      "text": "Then Eliphaz, the Themanite, answered, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:2",
      "text": "If we begin to speak to thee, perhaps thou wilt take it ill; but who can withhold the words he hath conceived?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:3",
      "text": "Behold thou hast taught many, and thou hast strengthened the weary hands:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:4",
      "text": "Thy words have confirmed them that were staggering, and thou hast strengthened the trembling knees:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:5",
      "text": "But now the scourge is come upon thee, and thou faintest: It hath touched thee, and thou art troubled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:6",
      "text": "Where is thy fear, thy fortitude, thy patience, and the perfection of thy ways?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:7",
      "text": "Remember, I pray thee, who ever perished being innocent? or when were the just destroyed?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:8",
      "text": "On the contrary, I have seen those who work iniquity, and sow sorrows, and reap them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:9",
      "text": "Perishing by the blast of God, and consumed by the spirit of his wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:10",
      "text": "The roaring of the lion, and the voice of the lioness, and the teeth of the whelps of lions, are broken:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:11",
      "text": "The tiger hath perished for want of prey, and the young lions are scattered abroad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:12",
      "text": "Now there was a word spoken to me in private, and my ears by stealth, as it were, received the veins of its whisper.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:13",
      "text": "In the horror of a vision by night, when deep sleep is wont to hold men,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:14",
      "text": "Fear seized upon me, and trembling, and all my bones were affrighted:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:15",
      "text": "And when a spirit passed before me, the hair of my flesh stood up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:16",
      "text": "There stood one whose countenance I knew not, an image before my eyes, and I heard the voice, as it were, of a gentle wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:17",
      "text": "Shall man be justified in comparison of God, or shall a man be more pure than his maker?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:18",
      "text": "Behold, they that serve him are not steadfast, and in his angels he found wickedness:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:19",
      "text": "How much more shall they that dwell in houses of clay, who have an earthly foundation, be consumed as with the moth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:20",
      "text": "From morning till evening they shall be cut down: and because no one understandeth, they shall perish for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.4.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:21",
      "text": "And they that shall be left, shall be taken away from them: they shall die, and not in wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
